description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you a qualified adult’s or children’s nurse/theatre practitioner or allied health professional dedicated to providing top quality care, but need the flexibility to match your individual circumstances?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Why not join the Temporary Staffing Bureau here at the University Hospitals Bristol NHS Foundation Trust today? You will benefit from working across all disciplines giving you the opportunity to gain experience in a wide range of specialties. Shifts are flexible, so you don’t need to commit to working hours that don’t suit you. It really doesn’t get any more convenient.Regular work is available and there is a the possibility of long and short term placements, so you can get the flexibility of temporary work combined with the team spirit and friendly atmosphere of a permanent role.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Make our bank your first choice and enjoy benefits, including:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Intensity bonuses&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Training Opportunities&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Holiday Pay&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;****PLEASE STATE THE POST FOR WHICH YOU ARE APPLYING IN THE SUPPORTING INFORMATION AND DESCRIBE IN SOME DETAIL YOUR EXPERIENCE AND TRAINING RELEVANT TO THE POST****&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;bankrecruitment@uhbristol.nhs.uk or Catherine.williams2@uhbristol.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
